South Korea have died from this outbreak, with 182 confirmed cases of infection. There", "score": "1.7625837"}}, "retrieval_3": {"pred": "true", "score": 1.9861850126575433, "ctx": {"id": "17804139", "title": "2012 Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus outbreak", "text": "MERS had infected at least 60 people with cases reported in Jordan, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates (UAE), Tunisia, Germany, the United Kingdom (UK), France and Italy, with a death toll of 38. Saudi officials expressed great concern that millions of Muslims from around the world would potentially be exposed to the virus during the autumn Hajj, or pilgrimage to Mecca. In May 2014, the WHO said it was monitoring the situation as global cases of MERS appeared to be on the rise, but said the situation did not yet constitute a health emergency. On 3 June 2014,", "score": "1.7133579"}}, "retrieval_4": {"pred": "true", "score": 1.9483086423405043, "ctx": {"id": "17804150", "title": "2012 Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus outbreak", "text": "and from that family at least one additional person presented similar symptoms but tested negative for the novel coronavirus. On 21 February 2013, WHO stated that there had been 13 laboratory-confirmed cases, 6 cases (4 fatal) from Saudi Arabia, 2 cases (both fatal) from Jordan, 2 cases from Qatar, and 3 from the UK. In March 2013, the Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health reported the death of a 39-year-old man, the 15th case and 9th death reported to WHO. On 2 May 2013, the Saudi Ministry of Health announced five people died and two other people were in critical condition", "score": "1.7122123"}}, "retrieval_5": {"pred": "true", "score": 1.9448819947308955, "ctx": {"id": "17804152", "title": "2012 Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus outbreak", "text": "73 to 85 years, but they have all chronic diseases.\" With this announcement, the unofficial global case count reached 49 while the death toll stands at 24 according to the CDC. As of